### Example 1: Domain \( x \in [0, 2] \)

#### Problem Setup
- **Heat Equation**: \( u_t = 3u_{xx} \)
- **Domain**: \( x \in [0, 2] \)
- **Boundary Conditions**: 
  - \( u(0,t) = 0 \)
  - \( u(2,t) = 0 \)
- **Initial Condition**: \( u(x,0) = \sin\left(\frac{\pi x}{2}\right) \)

#### MATLAB Code

```matlab
% Parameters
L = 2; % Length of the domain
T = 1; % Total time
Nx = 100; % Number of spatial points
Nt = 100; % Number of time steps
dx = L / (Nx - 1); % Spatial step size
dt = T / Nt; % Time step size

% Spatial grid
x = linspace(0, L, Nx);

% Time grid
t = linspace(0, T, Nt + 1);

% Initial condition
u0 = sin(pi * x / L);

% Initialize solution matrix
u = zeros(Nx, Nt + 1);
u(:, 1) = u0;

% Finite difference method
for n = 1:Nt
    for i = 2:Nx-1
        u(i, n+1) = u(i, n) + 3 * dt / dx^2 * (u(i+1, n) - 2*u(i, n) + u(i-1, n));
    end

    % Boundary conditions
    u(1, n+1) = 0;
    u(Nx, n+1) = 0;
end

% Plot initial condition
figure;
subplot(2, 1, 1);
plot(x, u0, 'LineWidth', 2);
title('Initial Condition: u(x,0) = sin(\pi x / 2)');
xlabel('x');
ylabel('u(x,0)');

% Plot solution at the final time
subplot(2, 1, 2);
plot(x, u(:, end), 'LineWidth',  2);
title(['Solution at t = ', num2str(T)]);
xlabel('x');
ylabel('u(x,T)');

% 3D surface plot of the solution over time
figure;
[X, T] = meshgrid(x, t);
surf(X, T, u');
shading interp;
title('Solution Surface: u(x,t)');
xlabel('x');
ylabel('t');
zlabel('u(x,t)');
colorbar;
```

