### MATLAB Code to Plot the Fourier Series with More Terms

Here is the updated MATLAB script to plot the Fourier series approximation for both \( N_{\text{terms}} = 10 \) and \( N_{\text{terms}} = 20 \):

```matlab
% Parameters
L = pi;
x = linspace(0, L, 1000); % Spatial grid

% Function to compute the Fourier series approximation
function u_approx = fourier_series(x, N_terms)
    u_approx = zeros(size(x));
    for n = 1:N_terms
        B_n = -4 / (n^3 * pi^3) * ((-1)^n - 1);
        u_approx = u_approx + B_n * sin(n * pi * x / L);
    end
end

% Compute the Fourier series approximation for N_terms = 10
N_terms_10 = 10;
u_approx_10 = fourier_series(x, N_terms_10);

% Compute the Fourier series approximation for N_terms = 20
N_terms_20 = 20;
u_approx_20 = fourier_series(x, N_terms_20);

% Plot the initial condition and the Fourier series approximations
figure;
hold on;

% Plot the exact initial condition
plot(x, x .* (L - x), 'r', 'LineWidth', 2, 'DisplayName', 'Exact Initial Condition');

% Plot the Fourier series approximation with N_terms = 10
